Package: RegCompassR
Title: GRN-First Multiome Reaction and Meta-Module Analysis
Version: 1.8.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "RegCompass", family = "Developers", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "dev@example.com"))
Author: RegCompass Developers [aut, cre]
Maintainer: RegCompass Developers <dev@example.com>
Description: Runs a species-aware human or mouse RNA+ATAC workflow that first normalizes single-cell RNA globally, computes ATAC TF-IDF within each cell type across conditions, and fits one Pando TF-peak-gene model per condition and cell type. Cells are then stratified only by condition for SuperCell2 metacell construction with gamma 75 by default, while an existing cell-type annotation is supplied as the SuperCell2 label to reduce cell-type mixing; each metacell also receives an unambiguous audited dominant cell-type label from its members for regulatory mapping. GRN and metacell condition-by-cell-type coverage is validated before condition-specific GRNs define complete-GPR core reactions, which are expanded through core-reaction subsystems and shared KEGG, Reactome, and master-Rhea identifiers, followed by local FASTCORE feasibility completion. Metacell RNA and ATAC evidence are integrated into reaction expression and directional COMPASS-like minimum-penalty scoring. Sample metadata are optional and are not used for balancing, selection, weighting, or grouping.
